11:47 a.m. Defendant Jonathan R. Stewart in court with attorney Bryce Alan Schoenborn. Mary Margaret Sowinski, Asst. DA, appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Calling 15TR3281,15TR2849,15TR2841. Sowinski speaks to agreement/resolution. State moves to dismiss Cts. 3,4,6,7 in 15CF158; dismiss 15TR3281 and 15TR2849; granted by the Court. Defendant pleads no contest to Cts. 1, 2, & 5 and 15TR2841. Court finds defendant guilty of OWI in 15TR2841 -- imposes forfeiture of $762, d.l. suspension for 6 mos., AODA and driver safety plan. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty of Cts. 1 & 5, defers entry for Ct. 2. Schoenborn statement to sentencing. Court questions defendant. All costs to be paid from bond.  The court informs defendant of right to request expungement of the DNA under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4).
